<h1>Digital Foundations</h1>

<h2>Course Overview</h2>
<p>
Digital Foundations is a comprehensive introductory course designed to equip learners with both theoretical understanding and practical skills required to navigate today’s technology-driven world. In modern society, digital literacy is no longer optional — it is a core life skill. From communication and education to business and security, digital systems influence nearly every aspect of our lives.
</p>

<p>
This course focuses on building a strong foundation by combining awareness, technical knowledge, and real-world application. Students will not only learn how computers and the internet work, but also how to use them responsibly, efficiently, and safely. By the end of the course, learners will feel confident interacting with digital tools, understanding online systems, and adapting to new technologies.
</p>

